    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Tuesday about possible plans by a Canadian pension fund to form a consortium and mount a $45 billion takeover bid for BCE, the parent company of Bell Canada, misstated the legal status of a rival company, Telus. While Telus had announced plans to convert to an income trust, it abandoned the move because of changes in the law.</p>
      </block>
